ENTRY       EC 3.1.13.2                 Enzyme
NAME        exoribonuclease H
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on ester bonds;
            Exoribonucleases producing 5'-phosphomonoesters
REACTION    3'-end directed exonucleolytic cleavage of viral RNA-DNA hybrid
COMMENT     This is a secondary reaction to the RNA 5'-end directed cleavage 13-19 nucleotides from the RNA end performed by EC 3.1.26.13 (retroviral ribonuclease H).
HISTORY     EC 3.1.13.2 created 1978, modified 2010
REFERENCE   1  [PMID:1691093]
  AUTHORS   Schatz O, Mous J, Le Grice SF
  TITLE     HIV-1 RT-associated ribonuclease H displays both endonuclease and 3'----5' exonuclease activity.
  JOURNAL   EMBO. J. 9 (1990) 1171-6.
